6db5d985-b0bc-577d-85b5-fc67f1a3d3a3,tg:rubgr:5351,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"

[2 bladen] [blad 1] Handwriting in Bruegel in Calumnia and Alchemist-but here more formal for prints, not sketchlike as in 'Naer het Leven'. Writing also in 'Beekeepers'. Problem of dark & light ink generally in Bruegel & followers; [blad 2] State new addidition to Bruegel's oeuvre. Handwriting of Bruegel. Elck, Alchemist, Beekeepers, Sins & Virtues, Temperantia by the stage, Ripa Grande (see Berlin exh. catal.), Calumnia, Basrode. All of these more or less formal. 'Naer het Leven' may have been added to distinguish from done from existing costume books - but who added it? The draughtsman or somebody else? Cat. 239 handwriting on left different. Naer het Leven - impossible by one hand - too many varieties in proportion which cannot be explained by the development of one artist. New group from darmstadt: 236-239 neither in Tolany or Münz. Add: problem of copies after Naer het Leven drawings; St. George's Gate problems [...][scan]
